CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1953, pg. 27, reads: "Novice Swim Meet - The City Recreation Department held its annual novice swimming meet last Thursday at Moore Pool in Brookline. The contestants in boys event included little Pomeroyal Fountain, shown in the left photo, poised for the start of a free-style event.  His late father was a champion swimmer and a recreation department employe [employee] for many years, and his son shows the same affinity for aquatic sports... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Boys, including Pomeroyal Fountain Jr. on end, posed at edge of swimming pool for City Recreation Department swim meet, at Moore Pool, Brookline
